IMF’s Lipsky Says U.S. ‘Certainly’ to See Increase in Debt Costs

-- B y   J e f f r e y   D o n o v a n
-- 
2011-09-23T11:54:23Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-23/imf-s-lipsky-says-u-s-certainly-to-see-increase-in-debt-costs.html
The U.S. will “certainly” see an
increase in debt-servicing costs in coming years, said  John
Lipsky , the International Monetary Fund’s former no. 2 official
and now a special adviser to the IMF chief.  He made his comments in an interview on Bloomberg
Surveillance radio with  Tom Keene  today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Jeffrey Donovan at 
 jdonovan26@bloomberg.net  